      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Tariffs are trade barriers imposed by governments to protect domestic industries by increasing the cost of imported goods. They can help create jobs and stimulate domestic production, but research shows they often have unintended consequences, such as reducing exports, increasing prices for consumers, and hurting other industries that rely on imported components. This is often referred to as the \"harm to consumers\" or \"retaliation\" effect, where domestic industries push for tariffs that benefit themselves but ultimately increase costs for end-users.",
