    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but isn't the \"long-term fix\" thing kind of a non-starter if the workers are losing everything right now? if a country's economy is built on these industries, wouldn't the most logical and moral thing for a government to do be to use tariffs to prioritize its own citizens over global market efficiency? it feels like the standard economic view is just fundamentally biased against the working class.",
