      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You're right that workers who face immediate hardship may be more concerned with a short-term solution than a long-term fix. The cultural narrative that prioritizes neoliberal \"global efficiency\" over worker interests can be seen as dismissive of the human costs of globalization. In reality, economic policies often apply the same rules to everyone, regardless of their impact on specific industries or workers. When governments are pressured to decide between competing interests, they may consider tariffs as a means to protect vulnerable populations, even if it means incurring economic costs.",
